12/12/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling Socialist Party opens its 6th national congress on Friday (12 December). 
The two-day conference is to elect the new chairman and members of the general committee, as well as to evaluate the activities of the party chairmanship over the past four years. 
The candidates for the chairman post are incumbent chairman and Prime Minister Fatos Nano, former President Rexhep Meidani and Tirana Mayor Edi Rama. 
The competition is seen as a crucial test for Nano and his policies. 
(ATA - 11/12/03)
